---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Words With Double Letters in Scrabble — High-Scoring Plays"
  description="Master high-scoring Scrabble words with double letters. BAZAAR, COFFEE, TOFFEE, BALLOON and more with point values. Strategy for premium square placement."
  keywords="double letter words scrabble, words with double letters, bazaar scrabble, coffee scrabble, toffee scrabble points, double letter strategy"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Words With Double Letters in Scrabble — High-Scoring Plays",
    "description": "Master high-scoring Scrabble words with double letters. BAZAAR, COFFEE, TOFFEE, BALLOON and more with point values and strategy.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-14",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/words-with-double-letters" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What are the highest-scoring double-letter words in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "PIZZAZZ scores 45 points with its double-Z. JAZZILY scores 35 points, BUZZING scores 28 points, and FIZZLE scores 27 points. Words with double high-value letters like Z (10), J (8), or X (8) score the most." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How do double-letter words work with premium squares?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "When one letter of a double pair lands on a Double Letter Score (DLS), only that single tile is doubled. For COFFEE, if one F lands on DLS, you add 4 extra points (F=4, doubled to 8). Double-Word Score (DWS) doubles your entire word score including both doubled letters." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What common words have double letters in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Common double-letter words include COFFEE (14 pts), TOFFEE (12 pts), BALLOON (9 pts), BASSOON (9 pts), AARDVARK (16 pts), COMMITTEE (15 pts), and BAZAAR (17 pts). Most use common tiles and are easily playable." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Double Letters</span>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Words With Double Letters in Scrabble</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-14">June 14, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>6 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        Double-letter words — words containing consecutive repeated letters like FF, ZZ, OO, or LL — are everywhere in English and pack serious scoring potential in Scrabble. When you draw duplicate tiles, these words turn what looks like a weak rack into a powerful play. BAZAAR uses your double-A, COFFEE deploys double-F, and TOFFEE combines both double-F and double-E. Here's everything you need to know about playing double-letter words for maximum points.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Double Letter Quick Stats</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">45</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Max Points (PIZZAZZ)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">ZZ</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Highest Double (10+10)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">FF</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Most Common Double</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">100+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid Words</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>The Scrabble tile bag contains multiples of most letters (12×E, 9×A, 9×I, 6×N, etc.), so drawing duplicates is extremely common. Rather than seeing doubles as wasted rack space, recognize them as keys to high-scoring plays that your opponent might not expect.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top Double-Letter Words by Points</h2>
      <p>Ranked by base point value. Words with double Z, X, J, or F score highest because those tiles carry premium values.</p>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-800">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">#</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Word</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Points</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Double</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Definition</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-800">
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">1</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">PIZZAZZ</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">45</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">ZZ</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Flair, vitality</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">2</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">JAZZILY</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">35</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">ZZ</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">In a jazzy manner</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">3</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">BUZZING</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">28</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">ZZ</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Making a humming sound</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">4</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">FIZZLE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">27</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">ZZ</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">To fail weakly</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">PUZZLER</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">27</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">ZZ</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Something that puzzles</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">MUZZLE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">26</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">ZZ</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Snout / to silence</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">DAZZLE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">25</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">ZZ</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">To blind with light</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">BAZAAR</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">17</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">AA</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Market or fair</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">9</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">AARDVARK</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">16</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">AA</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Burrowing mammal</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">MAMMOTH</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">16</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">MM</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Huge extinct elephant</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">11</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">BUFFOON</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">15</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">FF + OO</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Clown, jester</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">12</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">COMMITTEE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">15</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">MM + TT + EE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Group assembled to decide</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">13</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">COFFEE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">14</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">FF + EE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Brewed beverage</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">14</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">BAFFLE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">14</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">FF</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">To confuse</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">15</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">TOFFEE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">12</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">FF + EE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Sweet candy</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">16</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">RACCOON</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">11</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">CC + OO</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Masked mammal</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">17</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">BALLOON</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">9</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">LL + OO</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Inflatable object</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">18</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">BASSOON</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">9</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">SS + OO</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Musical instrument</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Premium Square Strategy for Doubles</h2>
      <p>Double-letter words have a unique advantage on premium squares: you can position the expensive half of the pair on the bonus square while the second identical letter rides free.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Z on DLS in DAZZLE</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">First Z on DLS = 20 pts from that tile alone. Second Z adds 10 more naturally. The ZZ pair contributes 30 of the word's 25 base points when DLS is used.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ F on TLS in COFFEE</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">One F on Triple Letter Score = 12 pts from that tile. Combined with the second F (4 pts), the FF pair alone contributes 16 points. Place high-value doubles on premiums.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ BAZAAR on DWS</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">BAZAAR (17 pts) on a Double Word Score = 34 points. The entire word including both A-A pairs gets doubled. DWS rewards longer words with premium letters.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ Low-value double on DLS</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Putting an L (1 pt) on DLS in BALLOON only adds 1 extra point. Prioritize placing the higher-value tile of the word on the premium square instead.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">LL</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">1+1 = 2</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">SS</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">1+1 = 2</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">EE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">1+1 = 2</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">OO</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">1+1 = 2</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">FF</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">4+4 = 8</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">ZZ</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">10+10 = 20</span>
        </span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Embrace duplicate tiles:</span> Drawing FF, ZZ, or MM isn't bad luck — it's an opportunity. COFFEE (14), BUZZING (28), and MAMMOTH (16) all require these "unwanted" duplicates. Know your double-letter words and turn liabilities into assets.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">ZZ words are game-winners:</span> With only one Z in the bag, ZZ words need a blank. But DAZZLE with blank-Z still scores 15 points base — and on premium squares, that can hit 45+. Worth saving your blank for.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">BAZAAR is your AA word:</span> With 9 A tiles in the bag, drawing 2+ A's is very common. BAZAAR (17 pts) uses them both productively while deploying the valuable Z (10 pts) and B (3 pts).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">TOFFEE and COFFEE are reliable:</span> Both use FF + EE — common duplicate draws. At 12 and 14 points respectively, they're solid 6-letter plays that don't need premium squares to be worthwhile.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Position expensive letters on premiums:</span> In DAZZLE, aim to put a Z on DLS (not the D or L). In COFFEE, target the F on premium squares. The cheap letters can fill gaps — premium squares should boost your highest-value tiles.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Related Articles -->
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/best-z-words-scrabble" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best Z Words in Scrabble — Top Scoring Z Plays</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/highest-scoring-scrabble-words" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Highest Scoring Scrabble Words Ever — Ultimate List</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/tile-distribution-explained" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Tile Distribution Explained — Every Letter Count</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-blue-800/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Try our free Scrabble Word Finder — instant results, no signup</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-400 text-gray-950 text-sm font-semibold transition-colors">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
